.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-PROXYARP 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.10.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-proxyarp \- proxy ARP configuration for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I proxyarp
file configures proxy ARP entries that allow the firewall to answer ARP
requests on behalf of hosts behind it.  Each entry causes the compiler to
emit the corresponding
.I ip neigh add proxy
commands (or equivalent) and to enable proxy_arp on the relevant interface.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/proxyarp
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ADDRESS	yes	IP address to proxy-ARP for
INTERFACE	yes	Interface on which to answer ARP requests
EXTERNAL	yes	External interface facing the requester
HAVEROUTE	no	Yes/No — whether a host route already exists
PERSISTENT	no	Yes/No — whether to survive firewall restarts
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Proxy ARP for a DMZ host visible on the external interface:
.RS
.nf
#ADDRESS       INTERFACE  EXTERNAL  HAVEROUTE  PERSISTENT
198.51.100.50  eth1       eth0      No         Yes
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-proxyndp (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-interfaces (5)

